{"cursor":"3633","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Sir Hormasji Peroshaw Mody' KBE (23 September 1881 - 9 March 1969), generally\nknown as 'Sir Homi Mody' was a noted Parsi businessman associated with Tata\nGroup and an administrator of India.\n\nHe started his career as a lawyer at Bombay and in 1913 became Chairman of\nBombay Municipal Corporation. In 1920 he joined business and became member of\nTextile Mill owners' Association of which he became Chairman in 1927. His\nsigning of Lees-Mody pact as its Chairman was subject of debate in Indian\nnationalist circle. [http://2ndlook.wordpress.com/tag/homi-\nmody/ Lees-Mody pact] He joined Tata Group as Director in 1939 and served\nthe group till 1959. He also served as director in various companies like - ACC,\nTata Hydro, Indian Hotels. He was Director of Central Bank of India\ntill 1968. [http://upgovernor.gov.in/modibio.htm] [-\nhttp://www.tatacentralarchives.com/history/biographies/08%20homimody.htm]\n\nHe was a member of Indian legislative Assembly for fourteen years from years\n1929 to 1943. In 1941 to 1943 he was appointed to the Viceroy's Executive\nCouncil with the key portfolio of Supply. He was member of Constituent Assembly\nof India for years 1948-1949. After independence of India, he was appointed as\nGovernor of United Provinces and Uttar Pradesh for the years 1949-52. He died on 9 March 1969, aged 87.\n\nAs an author he wrote books including: - (1) The Political Future of\nIndia ; Reflections (1908) (2) Biography of Feroz Shah Mehta Sir Pherozeshah\nMehta: a political biography, by Homi Mody (1963) (3) Wise and\nOtherwise. Homi Mody, a many splendoured life: a political biography by D.\nR. Manekar, 1968\n\nHe was the father of Russi Mody, Piloo Mody and Kali Mody.\n\nMody was knighted as a Knight Commander of the Order of the British Empire (KBE)\nin the 1935 Birthday Honours List, [http://www.london-\ngazette.co.uk/issues/34166/supplements/3612 London Gazette, 3 June 1935]\nand was appointed a Grand Commander of the Order of George I by George II, the\nKing of Greece in 1946 for services during the Second World War. [http://www.london-\ngazette.co.uk/issues/37670/pages/3887 London Gazette, 30 July 1946] A road\nin Mumbai is named after him as Sir Homi Mody Street.\n","linknr":132,"url":"Hormasji_Peroshaw_Mody","recorded":1375071481,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Homi_Mody&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Homi_Mody&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Homi_Mody","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Hormasji_Peroshaw_Mody&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire","/wiki/Parsi","/wiki/Tata_Group","#cite_note-z-1","/wiki/Bombay","#cite_note-z-1","#cite_note-2","/wiki/ACC_Limited","/wiki/Tata_Power","/wiki/Indian_Hotels_Company","#cite_note-a-3","/wiki/Central_Bank_of_India","#cite_note-a-3","#cite_note-x-4","/wiki/Central_Legislative_Assembly","/wiki/Viceroy%27s_Executive_Council","/wiki/Constituent_Assembly_of_India","/wiki/United_Provinces_(1937-1950)","/wiki/Uttar_Pradesh","#cite_note-a-3","#cite_note-a-3","#cite_note-5","#cite_note-6","/wiki/Russi_Mody","/wiki/Piloo_Mody","#cite_note-7","/wiki/Order_of_George_I","/wiki/George_II_of_Greece","/wiki/King_of_Greece","#cite_note-8","/wik